<.docs_layout active_guide="adopt">
  <.doc_heading
    title="Adopt the design system"
    description="Add the guidelines to any project - as AI guardrails, Phoenix rules, iOS tokens, or a single file. The Foundations and Styles pages are the human reference; these are the ways to pull them into your codebase."
  />

  <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-base-300 bg-muted/40 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
    One source of truth (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">usage-rules/*.md</code>),
    four ways to consume it. Pick the channel that matches your project.
  </div>

  <div class="mt-10 space-y-12">
    <%!-- 1. Claude plugin --%>
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Claude plugin - AI guardrails, any project
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        Installs a skill that auto-loads whenever you ask Claude to build, style, or
        review UI - so the guidelines apply without attaching a doc. Works in Claude
        Code, claude.ai, and the Agent SDK; covers both web and native iOS/iPadOS.
      </p>
      <.code_block
        language="claude"
        code={~S|/plugin marketplace add infinity-home-services/shadcn_daisyui_design
/plugin install shadcn-daisyui-design-system@shadcn-daisyui|}
      />
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        All ten reference files are bundled - nothing else to download. Update later with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">
          /plugin marketplace update shadcn-daisyui
        </code>. Prefer no plugin? Copy the skill folder into
        <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">.claude/skills/</code>
        from the <a
          href="https://github.com/infinity-home-services/shadcn_daisyui_design"
          class="link link-primary"
        >
          plugin repo
        </a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- 2. Phoenix usage_rules --%>
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Phoenix - sync the rules into AGENTS.md
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        If your app already depends on
        <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">shadcn_daisyui</code>
        (see <a href={~p"/docs/installation"} class="link link-primary">Installation</a>),
        sync its rules - component picking, forms, theming, and all ten design
        guidelines - into your
        <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">AGENTS.md</code>
        / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">CLAUDE.md</code>:
      </p>
      <.code_block
        language="shell"
        code={~S|# add the sync tool (dev only)
{:usage_rules, "~> 0.1", only: :dev}

mix deps.get
mix usage_rules.sync AGENTS.md --all|}
      />
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        Sync just this package with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">
          mix usage_rules.sync AGENTS.md shadcn_daisyui
        </code>, or a single guideline as a sub-rule, e.g. <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">
          shadcn_daisyui:foundations-spacing
        </code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- 3. Swift package --%>
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">iOS / iPadOS - the Swift token package</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        Add <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">ShadcnDaisyUI</code>
        via Swift Package Manager (the same semantic colors, spacing grid, radius
        scale, type ramp, motion, and elevation as the web theme - light and dark
        baked in):
      </p>
      <.code_block
        language="Package.swift"
        code={
          ~S|.package(url: "https://github.com/infinity-home-services/shadcn_daisyui_swift", from: "0.1.0")|
        }
      />
      <.code_block
        language="swift"
        code={~S|import ShadcnDaisyUI

Text("Settings").font(.sdPageTitle).foregroundStyle(Color.sdForeground)
  .padding(Spacing.s6)
  .background(Color.sdCard, in: .rect(cornerRadius: Radius.xl, style: .continuous))|}
      />
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        The package bundles these guidelines as
        <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">design-guidelines.md</code>
        and ships an
        <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">AGENTS.md</code>
        to drop into the Xcode project so AI stays on the rails there too.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- 4. One-file bundle --%>
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Any other project - one file</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        Every guideline concatenated into a single portable markdown file - drop it into
        any repo as the human + AI reference:
      </p>
      <.code_block
        language="shell"
        code={
          ~S|curl https://infinity-home-services.github.io/shadcn_daisyui/design-guidelines.md > DESIGN.md|
        }
      />
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        It's also the
        <a href={~p"/design-guidelines.md"} class="link link-primary">live bundle</a>
        linked from every Foundations and Styles page.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 flex items-center justify-between border-t border-base-300 pt-6 text-sm">
    <a href={~p"/docs/foundations/platforms"} class="link link-hover text-muted-foreground">
      ← Foundations
    </a>
    <a href={~p"/docs/installation"} class="link link-hover text-muted-foreground">
      Phoenix installation →
    </a>
  </div>
</.docs_layout>
